label.value: host immune system inflammatory response activated by pathogen present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system inflammatory response during pathogen infection is present. (GO:0006954 inflammatory response).

label.value: decreased host immune inflammatory response with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system inflammatory response during pathogen infection occurs to a lesser extent than normal. (GO:0006954 inflammatory response).

label.value: increased host immune inflammatory response with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system inflammatory response during pathogen infection occurs to a greater extent than normal. (GO:0006954 inflammatory response).

label.value: host defense-related protein involved in a pathogen interaction present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host defense-related protein usually present during infection is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased level of host defense-induced protein

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host protein usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased expression of a host defense-related protein involved in a pathogen interaction

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host defense-related protein usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: host cell viability with pathogen phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction cell level phenotype which affects the viability of a host cell in the presence of a pathogen.

label.value: host cell viable with pathogen

definition.value: A host cell viability phenotype where the host cell survives in the presence of the pathogen.

label.value: host cell inviable with pathogen

definition.value: A host cell viability phenotype where the host cell death is accelerated by the pathogen.

label.value: host defense-induced protein level phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of a host produced protein during infection.

label.value: host defense-induced RNA level phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of a host produced RNA during infection.

label.value: host physiological process affected by pathogen phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which a pathogen effects a change in the physiological processes of its host organism.

label.value: host hemorrhage with pathogen present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which host bleeding occurs during pathogen infection (MP:0001914 hemorrhage).

label.value: increased host hemorrhage with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the host bleeding during pathogen infection occurs to a greater extent than normal (MP:0001914 hemorrhage).

label.value: level of pathogen produced RNA within host phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of pathogen produced RNA during host infection.

label.value: presence of host gall during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the presence of a pathogen (or symbiont) has resulted in the abnormal growth of the host tissue, forming a plant gall (BTO:0005833 plant gall).

label.value: decreased number of host galls during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the presence of a pathogen (or symbiont) has resulted in a decreased number of plant galls (BTO:0005833 plant gall).

label.value: sensitive to calcium ion starvation

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to calcium ion starvation. Typically, individuals or populations are deemed sensitive to a stress if they stop growing (and may die) when exposed to the stress at an intensity that allows an individual or population of wild type cell(s) to grow and divide.

label.value: presence of pathogen sexual spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of sexual spores is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: stunted growth

definition.value: A single species growth phenotype where there is a decrease in size of an entire multicellular organism.

label.value: abnormal host morphology during phagocytosis of pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the host cell is irregular due to the phagocytosis (engulfment and ingestion) of the pathogen (GO:0006911).

label.value: host immune system phagocytosis of pathogen present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the host immune system activates the phagocytosis of a pathogen (GO:0006911).

label.value: presence of viable pathogen sexual spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the viability of sexual spores is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased number of host galls during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the presence of a pathogen (or symbiont) has resulted in an increased number of plant galls (BTO:0005833 plant gall).

label.value: presence of pathogen induced host DNA synthesis

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which host DNA synthesis occurs during pathogen infection (GO:0090592 DNA synthesis involved in DNA replication).

label.value: decreased pathogen induced host DNA synthesis

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the host DNA synthesis during pathogen infection occurs to a lesser extent than normal (GO:0090592 DNA synthesis involved in DNA replication).

label.value: abolished peptidase activity

definition.value: A single species molecular function phenotype in which a peptidase activity is absent.

label.value: increased pathogen induced host DNA synthesis

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the host DNA synthesis during pathogen infection occurs to a greater extent than normal (GO:0090592 DNA synthesis involved in DNA replication).

label.value: presence of host protein phosphorylation with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific host proteins, or of specific host protein sites, occurs during pathogen infection (GO:0006468 protein phosphorylation).

label.value: absence of host protein phosphorylation with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific host proteins, or of specific host protein sites, does not occur during pathogen infection (GO:0006468 protein phosphorylation).

label.value: increased host protein phosphorylation with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific host proteins, or of specific host protein sites, during pathogen infection occurs to a greater extent than normal (GO:0006468 protein phosphorylation).

label.value: decreased host protein phosphorylation with pathogen

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific host proteins, or of specific host protein sites, during pathogen infection occurs to a lesser extent than normal (GO:0006468 protein phosphorylation).

label.value: increased level of host defense-related RNA involved in a pathogen interaction

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host defense-related RNA usually present during infection is higher than normal.

label.value: presence of pathogen protein host DNA interaction

definition.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one pathogen protein to host DNA is present.

label.value: normal growth on tolnaftate

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to tolnaftate (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: resistance to tolnaftate

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the resistance of individuals or populations after exposure to tolnaftate. Typically, organisms are deemed resistant to a chemical if they survive at a concentration of the chemical that does not allow wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: sensitive to tolnaftate

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to tolnaftate. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: inhibition of pathogen polygalacturonase by host present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction molecular function phenotype in which host-mediated inhibition of a pathogen polygalacturonase is present.

definition.value:
A pathogen host interaction molecular function phenotype in which host-mediated inhibition of a pathogen polygalacturonase
occurs to a lesser extent than normal.

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to arborcandin C. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: normal growth on arborcandin C

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to arborcandin C (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal growth on pyrrolnitrin

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to pyrrolnitrin (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to pyrrolnitrin. label.value: resistance to pyrrolnitrin

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the resistance of individuals or populations after exposure to pyrrolnitrin. Typically, organisms are deemed resistant to a chemical if they survive at a concentration of the chemical that does not allow wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: resistance to osmotic stress

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the resistance of individuals or populations after exposure to an osmotic stress. Typically, individuals or populations are deemed resistant to a stress if they grow when exposed to the stress at an intensity at which an individual or population of wild type cell(s) stop growing (and may die).
